# Route the @octarq-org scope to GitHub Packages so a commercial build can install
# the published Pro plugin packages (@octarq-org/plugin-issuer, …). The workspace
# package @octarq/plugin-sdk resolves locally (workspace: protocol wins), so an
# OSS build never actually hits this registry.
#
# Auth is NOT set here on purpose: pnpm refuses to expand ${ENV} in a committed
# project .npmrc (it could leak a token to an attacker-controlled registry). CI
# provides auth at the user level instead — actions/setup-node with
# `registry-url: https://npm.pkg.github.com` writes an authenticated ~/.npmrc
# from NODE_AUTH_TOKEN. An OSS build needs no auth at all.
@octarq-org:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
